review:
... what's the funniest scene in a horror movie, ever?<br/><br/>"Oh wait, you have to let it breathe."
And then Hooper (the '70s guy, like Woody Allen, est, etc.) catches himself.<br/><br/>He just looks at him.
1.) The sharks killing people;
2.) The shark just ate a *kid*;
3.) The mayor believes us *now*;
4.) I can't *swim*;
5.) I'm supposed to be *retired*;
6.) The guy who's saving us is a *nut*, if he's saving us at *all*;
7.) We're going out into the *ocean* in a little *tin can* he calls a boat;
8.) Oh, and that tiger shark, you pulled a license plate out of? That's not a *great white*. That shark is *smaller*. This one is *bigger*.<br/><br/>Doesn't even look at him. Just fills it up -- it's a freakin' *goblet*, no less -- and starts talking to his wife.<br/><br/>Jeez Louise! What a day.<br/><br/>Great movie.
